FBIS3-58423 "drweu009_j_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Offers To Resign AU1301144294 Paris AFP in English 1427 GMT 13 Jan 93 AU1301144294 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Rome, Jan 13 (AFP) -- Italian Prime Minister Carlo Azeglio Ciampi offered his resignation Thursday [13 January] to President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro, a government official said. However, Scalfaro was expected to ask Ciampi to stay in office pending early general elections.
